  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.17-stable-8bbe7207`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI was under the impression that `eth_newPendingTransactionFilter` captures pending transactions as they go to the `txpool`.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nSome pending transactions appear in `txpool` without registering at `eth_newPendingTransactionFilter`.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. connect to a full node using `web3.js` (I also tried `web3py` and the Rust version) and start listening for a `eth_newPendingTransactionFilter`. \r\n2. Send test transactions to the full node.\r\n3. check that those transactions appear in the `txpool` by calling `txpool.inspect`\r\n4. wait for them to shown up in the filter, which would not happen",
